    <title>Open markdown file after running hexo new</title>
    <link href="https://ahodaisuki.github.io/posts/49575f16/"/>
    <id>https://ahodaisuki.github.io/posts/49575f16/</id>
    <published>2018-05-23T13:16:31.000Z</published>
    <updated>2018-06-01T15:58:10.052Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>For convenience!</p><h1 id="Solution"><a href="#Solution" class="headerlink" title="Solution"></a>Solution</h1><blockquote><p>You can try to listen to the new event  <a href="https://github.com/hexojs/hexo/issues/1007" target="_blank" rel="noopener">…More</a></p></blockquote><p>So, write a js file to do that. Get help from hexo plugins</p><blockquote><p>Hexo has a powerful plugin system, which makes it easy to extend functions without modifying the source code of the core module. There are two kinds of plugins in Hexo:<br><em>Script</em><br>If your plugin is relatively simple, it’s recommended to use a script. All you need to do is put your JavaScript files in the scripts folder and Hexo will load them during initialization.<br><em>plugin</em><br><a href="https://hexo.io/docs/plugins.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">…more</a></p></blockquote><h1 id="Environment-Info"><a href="#Environment-Info" class="headerlink" title="Environment Info"></a>Environment Info</h1><ul><li>hexo: 3.7.0</li></ul><h1 id="Quick-start"><a href="#Quick-start" class="headerlink" title="Quick start"></a>Quick start</h1><ol><li><p>Create script directory if it does’t exist in your blog root directory.</p><figure class="highlight sh"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="built_in">cd</span> yourblogi;</span><br><span class="line">mkdir script;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p>Create js file, filename you like. </p><figure class="highlight sh"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="built_in">cd</span> script;</span><br><span class="line">vi auto_openafterhexon.js;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p> Different operating system, the content is slightly different. On mac:</p><figure class="highlight js"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">var</span> spawn = <span class="built_in">require</span>(<span class="string">'child_process'</span>).spawn;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"> <span class="comment">// Hexo 3</span></span><br><span class="line">hexo.on(<span class="string">'new'</span>, <span class="function"><span class="keyword">function</span>(<span class="params">data</span>)</span>&#123;</span><br><span class="line">spawn(<span class="string">'vi'</span>, [data.path], &#123; <span class="attr">stdio</span>: <span class="string">'inherit'</span> &#125;);</span><br><span class="line">&#125;);</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p> About <em>stdio: ‘inherit’</em></p><blockquote><p>Because of the stdio: ‘inherit’ option above, when we execute the code, the child process inherits the main process stdin, stdout, and stderr. This causes the child process data events handlers to be triggered on the main process.stdout stream, making the script output the result right away.   <a href="https://medium.freecodecamp.org/node-js-child-processes-everything-you-need-to-know-e69498fe970a" target="_blank" rel="noopener">…More</a></p></blockquote></li><li><p>Save and exit js file above, enjoy.</p></li></ol><h1 id="Articles"><a href="#Articles" class="headerlink" title="Articles"></a>Articles</h1><ul><li>On windows: <a href="https://www.jianshu.com/p/5fbb62791f9b" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.jianshu.com/p/5fbb62791f9b</a> </li><li>Use another edit tool ( Sublime Text) on Mac: <a href="https://liam0205.me/2015/05/01/open-editor-after-hexo-new-immediately/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://liam0205.me/2015/05/01/open-editor-after-hexo-new-immediately/</a> </li></ul>]]></content>
    
